title: Alaskan Catch of BC Salmon
text:
Information on Alaskan exploitation of Skeena sockeye comes primarily from the Northern Boundary Sockeye Run Reconstruction model, which uses estimated run-timing and migration route to provide estimates of interception rates in Alaska fisheries. Data in and show timeseries of Alaskan exploitation for each Skeena sockeye Conservation Units with information (Figure 1) and the distribution of exploitation rates (Figure 2).








Figure 1: Alaskan exploitation rates for each Skeena sockeye Conservation Unit (1960-2023).













Figure 2: Alaskan exploitation rates on Skeena sockeye by CU.
